OL,3,CNewcastle United co-owner challenges
OL,4,C#36m bankruptcy petition in court
OL,6,FAccording to written submissions by Ms
OL,7,FStaveley's lawyer, Ted Loveday, his
OL,8,Fclient was told to sign various other
OL,9,Fdocuments and instruments between 2017
OL,10,Fand 2021, which ultimately said she
OL,11,Fwas personally liable and which
OL,12,Fincrementally topped up that liability.
OL,14,FMs Staveley claimed she felt
OL,15,Fintimidated into signing the documents
OL,16,Fand was left "worried for the safety
OL,17,Fof herself and her family".
