OL,6,FThe judge was told that Mr Restis'
OL,7,Flawyer, John Neocleous, allegedly told
OL,8,FMs Staveley that the shipping magnate
OL,9,F"was not a man to be messed with, that
OL,10,Fhe was dangerous and that (she) should
OL,11,Fnot cross him".
OL,13,FMr Loveday also said that Ms Staveley
OL,14,Fclaimed her Huntington's disease,
OL,15,Fwhich she allegedly made no secret of
OL,16,Ffrom Mr Restis or Mr Neocleous,
OL,17,Faffected her thinking and judgment.
