OL,6,FRaquel Agnello KC, a lawyer for Mr
OL,7,FRestis, said there is "no evidence" of
OL,8,F"undue influence or duress" or of any
OL,9,Funlawful conduct by her client and his
OL,10,Frepresentatives. Instead they argued
OL,11,Fthat Ms Staveley was given time to
OL,12,Flook over the documents and given
OL,13,Fopportunities to make revisions before
OL,14,Fsigning.
OL,16,FShe told the court there is no
OL,17,Fevidence "beyond (Ms Staveley's) bare
OL,18,Fassertion" that Mr Restis is a
OL,19,Fdangerous man.
